WEBVTT

01:38.832 --> 01:40.367
Check the heart line.

01:40.368 --> 01:42.135
Are you hyperventilating
the patient?

01:42.136 --> 01:43.604
No, doctor.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.939
Ready the bone wax.
Metzenbaum scissors.

01:46.940 --> 01:48.176
Metzenbaum scissors.

01:49.177 --> 01:50.777
Get that cat out of here.

01:50.778 --> 01:51.911
Yes, sir.

01:51.912 --> 01:53.513
Ready to close. Remove
the Weitlander retractor.

01:53.514 --> 01:55.148
We're closing, doctor.

01:55.149 --> 01:57.116
Remove the Raney clip,
for god's sake.

01:57.117 --> 01:58.518
I appreciate your letting me

01:58.519 --> 02:00.253
observe that
brain operation today.

02:00.254 --> 02:01.821
It would've
been more complicated

02:01.822 --> 02:02.989
if he'd needed one,

02:02.990 --> 02:05.358
but since you wanted to
observe my technique, I...

02:05.359 --> 02:07.560
That was very nice of you.
Doctor, were you, uh,

02:07.561 --> 02:10.263
were you interested
in science as a child?

02:10.264 --> 02:11.998
I don't know if I was interested

02:11.999 --> 02:13.266
so much in the science

02:13.267 --> 02:16.669
as I was the slime
that goes along with it.

02:16.670 --> 02:17.770
Snakes and frogs.

02:17.771 --> 02:20.973
When I saw how slimy
the human brain was, I...

02:20.974 --> 02:22.975
I knew that's what
I wanted to do

02:22.976 --> 02:24.344
with the rest of my life.

02:24.345 --> 02:25.912
What's the matter, Timon?

02:25.913 --> 02:27.714
I thought you liked fish.

02:27.715 --> 02:29.216
They taste funny.

02:29.217 --> 02:31.251
Really? It's fresh.

02:31.252 --> 02:33.086
It came right out of that tank.

02:34.555 --> 02:38.157
You hooked my angel fish?!

02:38.158 --> 02:42.295
Why do you do
these terrible things?

02:42.296 --> 02:45.064
Because I love
to see those veins

02:45.065 --> 02:47.133
in your temple throb.

02:47.134 --> 02:49.237
You... you...

02:50.271 --> 02:52.004
I'll kill you.

02:52.005 --> 02:53.673
Look here, you devil woman,

02:53.674 --> 02:56.142
you'll never do this
to another man!

02:56.143 --> 02:58.278
Oh, yes, I will.
I'll do it,

02:58.279 --> 03:00.580
and I'll do it,
and I'll do it again.

03:00.581 --> 03:02.081
Would you read that back to me?

03:02.082 --> 03:03.383
I'm afraid that might make me

03:03.384 --> 03:04.751
sound pompous to your readers.

03:04.752 --> 03:08.020
Uh, "my brilliant research
in brain transplantation

03:08.021 --> 03:09.456
"is unsurpassed

03:09.457 --> 03:12.459
and will probably make my name
live beyond eternity."

03:12.460 --> 03:14.060
No, that's all right.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.362
Take out the "probably."

03:15.363 --> 03:17.964
It makes me sound
wishy-washy.

03:17.965 --> 03:21.634
You take your hands off me,
you impotent prune!

03:21.635 --> 03:24.004
Ohh!

03:28.041 --> 03:30.810
My Renoir!
I'll kill you!

03:30.811 --> 03:33.346
I get so excited
when you get angry.

03:33.347 --> 03:34.581
It makes me feel so much closer

03:34.582 --> 03:36.349
to the reading of the will.

03:36.350 --> 03:38.351
You won't get a penny.

03:38.352 --> 03:41.187
I changed my will months ago.

03:41.188 --> 03:42.722
You son of a bitch.

03:42.723 --> 03:45.191
Well, I guess I'll
just have to find me

03:45.192 --> 03:46.426
a new man to torture.

03:46.427 --> 03:47.760
Dr. Furrier...

03:47.761 --> 03:49.128
That's... Hfuhruhurr.

03:49.129 --> 03:50.129
I'm sorry.

03:50.130 --> 03:51.197
That's all right.

03:51.198 --> 03:52.465
A lot of people mispronounce it,

03:52.466 --> 03:54.301
but it sounds just
the way it's spelled.

03:54.302 --> 03:59.071
H-f-u-h-r-u-h-u-r-r.
Hfuhruhurr.

03:59.072 --> 04:00.707
Hfuhruhurr-rur.

04:00.708 --> 04:03.476
That's good. You just went
a little past it there.

04:03.477 --> 04:06.346
Just put the brakes on
a little sooner.

04:06.347 --> 04:09.349
Doctor, I, uh...
I know you were quite shaken

04:09.350 --> 04:11.451
by the tragic death
of your wife.

04:11.452 --> 04:13.886
Oh, I couldn't talk
about it for a long while,

04:13.887 --> 04:17.490
but... Time passes by,
and I can handle it now.

04:17.491 --> 04:19.091
Her name was Rebecca.

04:19.091 --> 04:22.495
Why?! Why?! Why?! Why?!

04:22.496 --> 04:25.865
Is Ookums having
a massive heart attack?

04:25.866 --> 04:30.102
What a shame, with me
so young and hot!

04:30.103 --> 04:31.204
Pom-pom!

04:33.173 --> 04:34.775
Rip her throat out!

04:36.143 --> 04:38.779
Aah!

04:41.248 --> 04:44.250
Why?! Why?! Why?!
Why?! Why?! Why?!

04:44.251 --> 04:45.318
Dr. Furrier!

04:45.319 --> 04:47.387
Hfuhruhurr!

04:47.388 --> 04:49.722
I'm sorry.

04:49.723 --> 04:52.091
She was...

04:52.092 --> 04:53.693
Everything.

04:53.694 --> 04:55.362
Is that her?

04:55.363 --> 04:58.498
No. That's just
a statue of her.

04:58.499 --> 05:00.933
Our gardener Ramon, he...

05:00.934 --> 05:04.471
He made made that
for me after she...

05:04.472 --> 05:07.206
I love the way her head moves.

05:07.207 --> 05:10.943
She almost looks...
Alive.

05:10.944 --> 05:12.745
Watch out!

05:12.746 --> 05:14.415
Bye-bye!

05:29.363 --> 05:30.831
An angel.

05:32.199 --> 05:34.333
Little girl?

05:34.334 --> 05:35.735
Yes, sir?

05:35.736 --> 05:38.705
I want you to do something
very important, all right?

05:38.706 --> 05:39.972
OK.

05:39.973 --> 05:41.774
I want you to run home,
and I want you to call the E.R.

05:41.775 --> 05:44.777
of North Bank General Hospital,
932 1000.

05:44.778 --> 05:46.513
Tell them to set up O.R. 6 immediately

05:46.514 --> 05:49.148
and contact anesthesiologist
Isadore Tourick,

05:49.149 --> 05:51.784
472 2112, beep 12.

05:51.785 --> 05:53.886
Have them send an ambulance
with a paramedic crew,

05:53.887 --> 05:56.856
light IV, D-5 and W, KVO.
You got it?

05:56.857 --> 05:59.659
E.R., North Bank
General Hospital,

05:59.660 --> 06:01.193
932 1000.

06:01.194 --> 06:02.462
Set up O.R. 6,

06:02.463 --> 06:05.164
contact anesthesiologist
Isadore Tourick,

06:05.165 --> 06:07.834
472 2112, beep 12.

06:07.835 --> 06:10.336
Ambulance with paramedics
and light IV,

06:10.337 --> 06:12.371
D-5 and W, KVO.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.540
That's good.

06:13.541 --> 06:16.509
Sounds like a subdural
hematoma to me.

06:16.510 --> 06:17.777
Oh, it does, does it?

06:17.778 --> 06:19.546
Well, it's not your job
to diagnose.

06:19.547 --> 06:20.813
But I thought...

06:20.814 --> 06:22.615
You thought! You thought!
Just go!

06:22.616 --> 06:24.951
3 years of nursery school,
and you think you know it all!

06:24.952 --> 06:26.719
Well, you're still wet
behind the ears.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.689
It's not a subdural hematoma!
It's epidural! Hah!

06:29.690 --> 06:31.525
Goddamn, that makes me mad.

06:42.903 --> 06:45.838
I don't find this amusing,
Garrero!

06:45.839 --> 06:48.007
This is a better story
than I ever hoped for.

06:48.008 --> 06:49.909
Beautiful woman
gets hit by a car

06:49.910 --> 06:52.344
and needs brain surgery,
and the man who hits her

06:52.345 --> 06:53.913
is the world's greatest
brain surgeon

06:53.914 --> 06:55.582
who operates on her
and saves her life.

06:55.583 --> 06:57.550
If I save her life,
Olsen. If.

06:57.551 --> 07:00.019
You wanted to see me,
Dr. Brandon?

07:00.020 --> 07:01.187
Ah, yes, Michael.

07:01.188 --> 07:03.322
This operation that
you're about to perform,

07:03.323 --> 07:05.157
I feel,
is very ill-advised.

07:05.158 --> 07:07.193
No surgeon should ever
operate on a patient

07:07.194 --> 07:08.728
that he has personally injured.

07:08.729 --> 07:10.697
It would make him
too emotionally involved.

07:10.698 --> 07:12.599
Don't you think
I'm aware of that?

07:12.600 --> 07:14.000
But there's only one
other person I'd trust

07:14.001 --> 07:16.002
to perform this
operation... Beckermann.

07:16.003 --> 07:18.938
Dr. Beckermann was murdered
in Europe. You know that.

07:18.939 --> 07:19.972
Exactly!

07:19.973 --> 07:24.745
Not only is he dead,
he's 6,000 miles away.

07:30.884 --> 07:32.520
What is that?

07:34.755 --> 07:36.355
It's a vagina.

07:36.356 --> 07:38.357
I know what it is.

07:38.358 --> 07:40.292
I mean what are you doing?

07:40.293 --> 07:41.828
Shaving her.

07:41.829 --> 07:44.864
This is a brain operation.

07:44.865 --> 07:46.899
I know.

07:46.900 --> 07:48.901
What's that supposed
to be, a heart?

07:48.902 --> 07:50.670
Yes, sir.
Clive and I thought

07:50.671 --> 07:53.507
that since it's
Valentine's day that...

08:00.881 --> 08:03.049
You don't have to
shave her anywhere.

08:03.050 --> 08:04.651
We'll be using
my cranial screwtop

08:04.652 --> 08:06.252
method of entry into the brain.

08:06.253 --> 08:07.286
Fine. Yes, sir.

08:07.287 --> 08:09.689
I never want to see that again.

08:09.690 --> 08:11.691
I suppose if it were Christmas,

08:11.692 --> 08:13.927
you'd hang ornaments on it.

08:25.505 --> 08:27.608
