08:28.676 --> 08:31.144
Metzenbaum scissors.

08:36.249 --> 08:37.515
10-blade scalpel.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.318
10-blade.

08:39.318 --> 08:41.621
Sponge stick.

08:43.423 --> 08:46.159
Give me a little sweat
on my upper lip.

08:48.662 --> 08:50.097
Remove sweat.

09:00.173 --> 09:03.611
Cover her breasts.
I'm a man, flesh and blood.

09:07.681 --> 09:09.082
Scat!

09:09.883 --> 09:12.218
Damn!
The cats around here.

09:12.219 --> 09:14.888
Cranial screwtop.

09:28.869 --> 09:31.337
Now all we can do is wait.

09:31.338 --> 09:32.873
Yes.

09:45.052 --> 09:47.153
Where am I?

09:47.154 --> 09:49.622
In a hospital.
You've had an accident.

09:49.623 --> 09:51.924
Oh.

09:51.925 --> 09:54.393
I hope I haven't
caused any trouble.

09:54.394 --> 09:56.362
Oh, no.

09:56.363 --> 09:57.797
I'm so tired.

09:57.798 --> 09:59.632
Shh shh shh shh.

09:59.633 --> 10:01.033
Who are you?

10:01.034 --> 10:03.135
Oh,
I'm... I'm your doctor.

10:03.136 --> 10:04.004
I want...

10:04.005 --> 10:06.173
Oh, don't...
Don't try and talk.

10:13.346 --> 10:14.346
Doctor.

10:14.347 --> 10:15.514
Huh?

10:15.515 --> 10:18.718
You're wanted in O.R. 6
in 5 minutes.

10:18.719 --> 10:20.020
Thank you.

10:22.422 --> 10:24.958
Ohh. Continue
the Dilantin IV.

10:53.386 --> 10:55.222
What a skull.

10:59.059 --> 11:00.693
Ohh.

11:00.694 --> 11:04.031
Boy, would I like
to jump on those bones.

11:05.198 --> 11:06.700
Rebecca.

11:08.168 --> 11:10.903
I can't help
comparing her to you.

11:10.904 --> 11:12.905
She has a behind so sexy

11:12.906 --> 11:15.775
you'd like to eat lunch off it.

11:15.776 --> 11:18.745
Just like we did, remember?

11:18.746 --> 11:21.013
Rebecca.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.449
I've had the top
of her head off,

11:23.450 --> 11:25.818
but that's as far as it went.

11:25.819 --> 11:28.587
I promise I'll never recite
our favorite poem

11:28.588 --> 11:31.490
to anyone but you.

11:31.491 --> 11:33.426
In Dilman's grove.

11:34.627 --> 11:38.765
In Dilman's grove,
my love did die,

11:38.766 --> 11:41.468
and now in ground,
she'll ever lie.

11:42.635 --> 11:46.172
None could e'er
replace her visage,

11:46.173 --> 11:48.074
until your face

11:48.075 --> 11:49.943
brought thoughts of kissage.

12:03.723 --> 12:06.092
Nurse.

12:06.093 --> 12:07.659
Good.
I'm glad you're here.

12:07.660 --> 12:08.761
Make a note.

12:08.762 --> 12:11.931
Right arm grip strength
very good.

12:11.932 --> 12:15.769
Left arm's... there's
just no improvement.

12:19.439 --> 12:23.110
I went out
and got you a little present.

12:26.513 --> 12:29.883
"The complete poems
of John Lilyson."

12:32.219 --> 12:34.720
"England's greatest
one-armed poet"?

12:34.721 --> 12:36.688
He wrote in Dilman's grove

12:36.689 --> 12:39.391
and pointy birds.

12:39.392 --> 12:40.894
I...

12:44.832 --> 12:46.098
"oh, pointy birds,

12:46.099 --> 12:48.700
"oh, pointy, pointy,

12:48.701 --> 12:50.569
"anoint my head,

12:50.570 --> 12:51.971
anointy, 'nointy."

12:51.972 --> 12:54.440
He died in 1894.

12:54.441 --> 12:58.477
He was the first person
ever to be hit by a car.

12:58.478 --> 13:01.713
To think you were
almost killed by a car.

13:01.714 --> 13:03.515
Michael.

13:03.516 --> 13:05.385
That's all over now.

13:07.287 --> 13:09.721
That man you ran away
from that night...

13:09.722 --> 13:11.925
Poor old Mr. Creswell.

13:14.227 --> 13:17.197
It was all my fault, in a way.

13:18.265 --> 13:22.001
I never should have
gone there alone.

13:22.002 --> 13:24.536
I guess I'm just too trusting.

13:24.537 --> 13:27.007
Oh, poor little bird.

13:28.341 --> 13:30.409
So fragile.

13:30.410 --> 13:32.611
So naive.

13:32.612 --> 13:34.313
So childlike.

13:34.314 --> 13:36.482
So shy.

13:36.483 --> 13:38.817
So chaste.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.453
So innocent.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.024
Rebecca.

13:45.025 --> 13:46.292
If there's anything wrong

13:46.293 --> 13:48.827
with my feelings for Dolores,

13:48.828 --> 13:50.229
just give me a sign.

13:50.230 --> 13:52.498
No!

13:52.499 --> 13:54.200
No!

13:54.201 --> 13:56.302
No!

13:56.303 --> 13:57.636
No!

13:57.637 --> 13:59.438
No!

13:59.439 --> 14:01.373
No!

14:01.374 --> 14:03.109
No!

14:03.110 --> 14:04.643
No!

14:04.644 --> 14:06.812
No!

14:06.813 --> 14:08.414
No!

14:08.415 --> 14:10.149
No!

14:10.150 --> 14:11.817
No!

14:11.818 --> 14:14.053
No!

14:14.054 --> 14:16.755
Just any kind of sign.

14:16.756 --> 14:20.026
I'll keep on the lookout for it.

14:20.027 --> 14:22.228
Meanwhile, I'll just
put you in the closet.

14:22.229 --> 14:24.663
In sickness or in health

14:24.664 --> 14:27.333
till death do you part?

14:27.334 --> 14:28.334
I do.

14:28.335 --> 14:32.104
I now pronounce you
man and wife.

14:32.105 --> 14:34.141
You may kiss the bride.

14:40.413 --> 14:42.115
Not now.

14:59.466 --> 15:02.701
There it is, darling.
Your new home.

15:02.702 --> 15:06.138
The house of hfuhruhurr.

15:06.139 --> 15:09.075
What are those assholes
doing on the porch?

15:09.076 --> 15:12.644
Those aren't assholes.

15:12.645 --> 15:14.982
It's pronounced "azaleas."

15:16.683 --> 15:19.851
I put them there for you.

15:19.852 --> 15:21.253
Señor.

15:21.254 --> 15:23.855
No, Ramon.
My wife will not be

15:23.856 --> 15:26.059
entering her new home
in a wheelchair.

15:41.841 --> 15:44.611
I want this moment
to last forever.

15:52.752 --> 15:54.786
Señor?

15:54.787 --> 15:58.390
Señor, would you like to
eat your breakfast now?

15:58.391 --> 16:00.092
Have you taken enough
photos of the moment

16:00.093 --> 16:02.594
so we can remember
this moment forever?

16:02.595 --> 16:03.496
Oh, yes.

16:03.497 --> 16:05.497
And we got them
back already. See?

16:05.498 --> 16:06.632
Oh, that's nice.

16:06.633 --> 16:09.101
All right, breakfast.

16:09.102 --> 16:11.171
We'll get cleaned up first.

16:13.873 --> 16:15.874
One of my favorite people
in the world

16:15.875 --> 16:18.044
is about to walk out here.

16:18.045 --> 16:20.412
I'm happy to say he is
still busy making his...

16:20.413 --> 16:22.514
Look, I framed the moment.

16:22.515 --> 16:23.649
Mm-hmm.

16:23.650 --> 16:26.718
He's now about to
unveil his latest picture,

16:26.719 --> 16:28.520
which I hear is just amazing,

16:28.521 --> 16:30.857
opening on the 21st
of this month...

16:38.031 --> 16:39.598
Yuck.

16:39.599 --> 16:40.999
Wait. Turn that back.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.000
That's my favorite movie.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.569
That's Donovan's brain.

16:43.570 --> 16:45.637
And not the slightest
sign of decay?

16:45.638 --> 16:48.107
None. I've never seen
healthier tissue.

16:48.108 --> 16:50.642
It's growing larger by the day.

16:50.643 --> 16:52.878
It's disgusting.

16:52.879 --> 16:54.913
Brains are so ugly.

16:54.914 --> 16:56.216
No. It's beautiful.

16:57.817 --> 16:59.218
I'm late!

16:59.219 --> 17:01.253
Is that all you're
gonna have for breakfast?

17:01.254 --> 17:02.854
It's all I have time for.

17:02.855 --> 17:04.123
How do you feel?

17:04.124 --> 17:05.824
Oh, I'm fine.

17:05.825 --> 17:08.727
I just... Wish I could
get out of this wheelchair

17:08.728 --> 17:11.597
so I could help a little
around the house.

17:11.598 --> 17:12.565
You will.

17:12.566 --> 17:14.233
You just had a major operation.

17:14.233 --> 17:16.034
It takes time to recover.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.203
You're gonna be up
and around in no time.

17:17.204 --> 17:18.771
Just be patient.

17:20.740 --> 17:23.510
Dolores? Soon?

17:25.778 --> 17:27.547
Huh?

17:30.016 --> 17:31.017
Huh?

17:54.241 --> 17:55.707
Forgot my hat.

17:55.708 --> 17:56.942
Ooh! Ohh!

17:56.943 --> 18:00.112
You walked! You walked!
You walked!

18:00.113 --> 18:03.482
I shouldn't have gotten up,

18:03.483 --> 18:04.883
but I wanted to surprise you

18:04.884 --> 18:07.586
and walk into your arms
tonight when you came home.

18:07.587 --> 18:11.223
You walked! You walked!
You walked!

18:11.224 --> 18:13.359
I love you so much.

18:13.360 --> 18:14.893
Who is that man out there?

18:14.894 --> 18:17.028
Juan.
He works for Ramon.

18:17.029 --> 18:18.797
Oh. He frightened me.

18:18.798 --> 18:21.500
He's just a big,
good-natured bag of muscles.

18:21.501 --> 18:25.036
There's just something about him
that makes me quiver.

18:25.037 --> 18:26.772
Is he here often?

18:26.773 --> 18:28.607
Just one day a week.

18:28.608 --> 18:29.841
What day?

18:29.842 --> 18:31.343
Tuesday.

18:31.344 --> 18:32.811
Is he ever alone?

18:32.812 --> 18:37.883
I mean, does Ramon ever go off
and leave him here alone?

18:37.884 --> 18:39.385
Sometimes. Why?

18:39.386 --> 18:41.653
I'd like to know.

18:41.654 --> 18:45.791
Please, tell Ramon to warn me

18:45.792 --> 18:49.228
when he's gonna leave me
alone with that Juan person.

18:49.229 --> 18:51.663
All right, if that'll
make you feel better.

18:51.664 --> 18:53.965
That'll make me
feel much better.

18:53.966 --> 18:56.803
Frightened little mouse.

19:02.742 --> 19:04.276
I'll tell Ramon

19:04.277 --> 19:07.614
to warn her about Juan.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.217
Ramon!

19:11.218 --> 19:14.052
Michael, Michael,
how is married life?

19:14.053 --> 19:15.053
I don't know!

19:15.054 --> 19:17.055
I'm sorry.
I've been on edge

